      <Docs>
        <param name="xml">XML data to convert into a hash table.</param>
        <summary>Parses and converts an XML string such as Microsoft Office InfoPath workflow form data into a hash table.  </summary>
        <returns>The hash table representation of the XML data that was passed in. </returns>
        <remarks>
          <para>Keys in the hash table are matched to the top-level schema nodes in the XML.</para>
          <para>The <see cref="M:Microsoft.Office.Workflow.Utility.Form.XmlToHashtable(System.String)" /> method creates only one level of hash table. It converts tags as keys and values of type <b>string</b>. In the following code examples, the XML data (first code example), gives you the hash table (second code example). where the following is specified:</para>
          <list type="bullet">
            <item>
              <description>ht["a"] is the value "aaa" as string.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
              <description>ht["b"] is the value "bbb" as string</description>
            </item>
            <item>
              <description>ht["c"] is the value "&lt;d&gt;ddd&lt;/d&gt;" as string.</description>
            </item>
          </list>
          <code>&amp;lt;data&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;a&amp;gt;aaa&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;b&amp;gt;bbb&amp;lt;/b&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;c&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;d&amp;gt;ddd&amp;lt;/d&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;/c&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/data&amp;gt;</code>
          <code>Hashtable ht = XmlToHashtable(data);</code>
          <para>For an example of how to use the <see cref="M:Microsoft.Office.Workflow.Utility.Form.XmlToHashtable(System.String)" /> method, see the example in ExpandGroups method.</para>
          <para />
        </remarks>
